newsitem.title: AUSTRALIA: RTRS-AWB says has total 180,000 T in Pakistan deal.
newsitem.headline: RTRS-AWB says has total 180,000 T in Pakistan deal.

text.p: The Australian Wheat Board (AWB) said on Monday its total sale of wheat to Pakistan in the latest tender was 180,000 tonnes.
As previously reported, Australia and the U.S. each won tonnages in the Pakistan tender for a total 315,000 tonnes of white wheat.
An AWB reference last week to it winning 112,000 tonnes in the latest Pakistan tender was to one shipping component of the sale, an AWB spokesman said on Monday.

The AWB said on Monday that its total sale of 180,000 tonnes was sold at A$193 a tonne fob-equivalent and that the U.S., for its 135,000 tonnes sale in the same tender, received a price equivalent to A$192 a tonne.
CITIC Food Australia, which handled 45,000 tonnes of the AWB sale to Pakistan, last week said the AWB sale of Australian Standard White to Pakistan was priced at US$156.285 a tonne.
